config BR2_PACKAGE_GPIO
	bool "IDL GPIO Modules/Userspace"
	select BR2_PACKAGE_PAL_OSAL
	default y
	help
	  Kernel modules and tools for the IDL GPIO. They are
	  used by arris_wlan_rpc_server and until I can get
	  rid of it they must be installed for a smooth start.
	  Note they do not require IDL to be installed in fact
	  IDL requires them. Includes WPS_GPIO for now.

	  IDL GPIO
	  ========
	  Files tagged:
	  $(find -name '*gpio*')

	  Most people should answer Y.

